<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Unabridged</ENAMEX> .  Although direct comparison between the
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Longman Dictionary</ENAMEX> of the <ENAMEX TYPE="LANGUAGE">English Language</ENAMEX> [hereafter
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">L</ENAMEX>] and the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">W</ENAMEX> reveals many similarities, there are
many differences, too.  <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">One</NUMEX> gets the impression that
the <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">editors</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">L</ENAMEX> used the good stuff from the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">W</ENAMEX> and
substituted their own, much better material when
